        "description": "MSSQL query performance and blocking triage dashboard. Pick a SqlServer instance from the left to scope every panel to that instance. Three vertical stripes: (1) what is slow \u2014 query heatmap and sortable query list; (2) who is stuck \u2014 active and blocked session counts plus a wait-type breakdown (the closest available proxy for a per-session blocker view, since the adapter does not surface individual sessions as VCF Ops resources); (3) what is the box doing \u2014 CPU usage, page life expectancy, and disk latency. Disk latency charts (H, I) show per- SqlDatabase metrics because read/write latency is not available at the SqlServer level; see TOOLSET GAP note below.\nLayout adapted from brockpeterson/operations_dashboards/Legacy MSSQL Dashboards.zip (MS-SQL-DBA-Overview.json, MS-SQL-Query-Analysis.json) \u2014 layout and interaction pattern reference only; metric keys have been re-verified against the SqlServerAdapter describe cache.",
